__NAME__ purpose
define options types and behavior
__END__

__NAME__ example: Find and add a new option type
<programlisting>
Options Module table modules
</programlisting>
That will cause a require of <literal>Vend::Options::Module</literal>.
__END__

__NAME__ example: Change default display type for Matrix widgets
<programlisting>
Options Matrix display_type separate
</programlisting>
__END__

__NAME__ example: Disable old Interchange 4.8 options
<programlisting>
Options Old48 disable 1
</programlisting>
__END__

__NAME__ see also
OptionsEnable
__END__